<activity><title>Standard Form</title>
<task><p>Follow the steps to write the equation  
    <me>4x^2-6y^2+16x-12y-14=0</me>
  in standard form.</p> 
<p>Collect the <m>x</m>-terms and <m>y</m>-terms together.
    <me><fillin characters="16"/> = 14</me></p>                                               
<p>Factor out the coefficients of <m>x^2</m> and <m>y^2</m>. Be careful:  you are factoring a 
    negative number from the <m>y^2</m>-terms.                
    <me><fillin characters="16"/> = 14</me></p>
<p>Complete the square in <m>x</m> and in <m>y</m>. Be careful! Notice that you have really added <m>4(4) = 16</m> to 
the <m>x</m>-terms and <m>-6(1) = -6</m> to the <m>y</m>-terms on the left side of the equation.</p> 
<p> Simplify each side.</p>
<p>Divide both sides by the constant, and simplify.</p></task>
</activity>

